title: For Sale:  UPDATE- 1942 Colt Commando 4" -Wood Grips-Holster
postcontent: 1942 Colt Commando 4" - Wood Grips - HolsterDescriptionWhat we have here is a great old Colt revolver, and a piece of WWII life history.The Colt Commando was a variation of the Colt Official Police revolver, produced to fulfill military needs for WWII, between 1941 and 1945.This particular .38 Special revolver, Serial Number 4023, is an early production gun from the Commando model series ---- manufactured in 1942 in Hartford CT, according to Colt's Manufacturing database records.There were approximately 50,000 manufactured in total.From various information sources publicly available for these Commandos, I speculate that this gun was originally purchased by the government, through the DSC (Defense Supplies Corporation). From research done by Charles Pate, "The DSC had the role of providing arms for defense plant guards, police departments and security personnel of various government organizations."From the DSC, I believe this revolver became the property, and daily companion of a Mr. N (to preserve privacies), who was a security guard at Crucible Steel in Syracuse, NY, during the war years, through his retirement in perhaps the '70s.I believe it passed from that gentleman's ownership, to the hands of its current owner.This gun is in great functional and cosmetic shape.It has: 4" barrel with great Like New shiny crisp bore and sharp crown probably 90% original parkerized finish - very well taken care of in daily use Great condition Walnut Grips with Colt Pony logo inlays in both grips - normal holster and service duty wear. Due to its early production, it was outfitted with Colt checkered wooden grips with Colt Pony logo silver medalions embedded in each grip. These grips were at the time used for the civilian Colt Official Police revolvers - and apparently used on the early Commandos until the standard molded plastic grip could become available in adequate supply. US Government inspectors Flaming Ordnance Bomb stamp on upper left frame corner  Colt Verified Proof Mark (P inside a V) on lower left frame forward of the trigger Another Colt factory inspector's stamp at left rear trigger guard frame ( appears to be 'Y' ?) Another Colt inspector 'L' stamp below the SN mark on the frame under ejector rod Also included is a very nice Audley Holster - patented Oct 13, 1914 - which has apparently been with this revolver since its days at Crucible Steel.I welcome any corrections or helpful info for any of my efforts to fill in truthful history for this revolver!Please see the pics - they show a number of other assemblers marks, and the true condition of this wonderful firearm.SpecificationsManufacturer: Colt's Manufacturing Model: CommandoAction: SA/DA RevolverFinish: ParkerizedS/N: 4023Caliber: .38 SpecialCapacity: 6-round cylinderBarrel: 4"Payment InformationPayment may be made by Money Order or other form of certified check. I also welcome any corrections or helpful info for any of my listings!Use the GunBroker.com contact seller link to initiate first contact with me.I'll respond to all inquiries as quickly as possible.

postcontent: Pedersoli Howdah muzzle loading black powder 20 gauge double barrel smoothbore pistol.  Like new, never fired. Called a "Howdah" because guns like these were carried by 19th century tiger hunters riding in howdahs, which is what the saddle and canopy mounted on the back of an elephant is called. If a tiger attacked the elephant, then the hunter could shoot it at close range using a large caliber pistol. This pistol will shoot either a .614 ball or can be loaded with shot. Both bores are smooth bores. Beautiful wood and engraved metal - both a shooter and a display piece. With original box; the box has a few dings from shipping, but the gun is in perfect shape. title: For Sale:  STAINLESS Compact 9 mm Kahr
postcontent:
This gun strikes the perfect balance of size, versatility, and comfort.
It has a very unique slim profile with 8+1 capacity in a concealable 9 mm package – it distinguishes itself this way in a sea of look-a-like pistols. An almost brilliant design: small and light for concealed carry – but large enough for comfortable use at the range.
* This item is for sale.  It is not necessary to ask if it is still available.  If you are reading the ad, it is available.
 (No trades. No silly low offers -- these messages will not be returned.)
FEATURES:- Great Workmanship & High Quality:   Slides and barrels are machined from stainless steel instead of carbon steel. The slide release is an actual dimensionally manufactured part versus being a stamped part. The trigger is metal versus being polymer, as is the magazine. Even the recoil spring is a stainless double captive spring recoil assembly. Excellent quality that rivals much higher end guns for the price.- Stone cold reliability: all the safety benefits of a Glock, but without the awkward, spongey trigger safety. Simple fire control mechanism for excellent reliability! Pulling the trigger disengages the passive striker block safety, finishes cocking the gun and then completes the firing cycle by releasing the spring loaded firing pin. It is an extremely safe design which in many ways works more like a revolver then a striker fired pistol.- Trigger feel is excellent and similar to a really light, smooth, crisp double action Smith revolver than a striker-fired pistol.  Often sited as the best trigger break in any striker-fired pistol in its class – clean and crisp.- Trigger cocking locked breech “Browning-type” recoil lug design. Pulling the trigger disengages a passive striker block safety, further cocks the gun, and then completes the firing cycle by releasing the spring loaded firing pin. It is an extremely safe design, which in many ways works more like a revolver then a striker fired pistol.- Double recoil spring assembly makes the gun easy to manually cycle and charge. - Single stack magazine makes the gun SLIM -- easy to conceal and easy to handle for those with small to medium hands (or those who just a more compact feel). So slim that you would think it is 380 caliber instead of a 9 mm.- Ergonomic very similar to a 1911 but it somehow cleaner and more comfortable. Very similar to a compact 1911 commander feel. Grips are not over-textured and come with very pleasant feeling front and back straps.- Perfect size: large enough to be comfortable at the range, but slim enough on profile to be light and comfortable to conceal.- Capacity: 8 + 1
